<br>
If I group with a pickup group or with strangers I always provide temperance, and rezzes, free of charge. If I don't like playing with someone then I add them to my avoid list, but if I agree to group then I had better do everything I can to keep them alive.  Sometimes I eat the cost with no exp or loot, so I just go kill everything in Crushbone to feel better, and summon lots of bread and water.<br>
<br>
It is true that spells are incredibly expensive, but because I have been willing to help others I find that others are willing to help me go hunt for components or spell drops. I know I am not going to afford getting every spell for every level, but I am still able to help my friends and enjoy the time I spend with them. I am always poor but I am still having fun, and I can always eat bread and water *gag* *choke*.<br>
<br>
If you are going to remain a cleric then it will be necessary to find yourself in the role or you will never enjoy it. In my opinion. <br>
<br>
Standard disclaimer: I suck. And I am stupid. And I dress funny. And I am a bad cleric. And anyone that groups with me is doomed. Doomed!<br>
