<br>
The group should not have to contribute to your KEI fund. I do not make my group pay me for my KEI. It is part of the expenses, for me, in leveling and getting experience. If 50 pp is too expensive for you, donate 20, or 30, or 40 pp instead. (And if I misunderstood what you meant by including how much KEI costs you in your itemization, I appologize, but it looked like you were saying that this is part of the cost that should be compensated for having you in the group <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> )<br>
<br>
As for Temp (or Virtue) or ANY symbol for that matter that costs a component, I completely and heartily agree that the cleric should be reimbursed. Rinjai now gets paid for his dots that he spends when we go out adventuring, even if he's casting it on normal group -- this is only fair, since most of the rest of us don't have to spend components to use buffs.<br>
<br>
I would suggest perhaps, that if folks don't pay you a peridot (or whatever component is needed for the lower levels) that they simply do not get buffed with the buff that requires that component. (Or pp equivilent for it). It is not fair to clerics to make them pay extra to level up and help the group, when the benefit of having a cleric in your group is often of vital importance. If there are people in your group unwilling to accomodate the cleric in this way, let them get a druid buff, or a shield buff from some class that doesn't need to pay out a reagent. It is not a requirement for the cleric to cast the shield buffs and any group that thinks so can go find another healer if they can find one, if they think they should be getting freebies.<br>
<br>
