<br>
mages can summon neck items that have a chance to make you not use a component, and shoulder items that make your buffs last longer.<br>
<br>
'course i typically don't remember to point out to the cleric in my groups that i can do this until after temp has been cast, but it is a good thing to keep in mind and may help bring down costs some.<br>
<br>
and i typically sell my mage toys for donotions, and that's what they are.  i'll take food, copper, pp, pretty much anything, i dont expect a lot since it doens't cost a component but to help cover my expensive spells a little something is nice.  if someone asks me how much, i'll always say whatever you feel is right. <p>Zanya Darkblood<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><br>
